.TH DFMGR "1" "February 2026" "dfmgr 202602020740-git" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
dfmgr \- DotFiles ManaGeR for installing and managing user configuration files
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B dfmgr
[\fI\,OPTIONS\/\fR] [\fI\,COMMAND\/\fR] [\fI\,CONFIG\/\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B dfmgr
is a comprehensive dotfiles management system for installing, updating, and managing user configuration files across various applications. It provides a unified interface for managing dotfiles from preconfigured GitHub repositories, making it easy to maintain consistent configurations across multiple systems.
.PP
dfmgr supports over 60 different application configurations including terminal emulators, text editors, window managers, shells, media players, and development tools. Each configuration package includes properly formatted dotfiles, installation scripts, and necessary symlinks.
.PP
The tool supports installation from the dfmgr organization repositories on GitHub, automatic updates via cron scheduling, search functionality for discovering available configurations, and proper version tracking.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B personal
Manage personal dotfiles repository (custom user configurations)
.TP
.B list
List currently installed dotfile configurations
.TP
.B search \fI\,<term>\/\fR
Search for available dotfile configurations matching the specified term
.TP
.B available
Show all available dotfile configurations from the repository
.TP
.B install \fI\,<config>\/\fR
Install a dotfile configuration package
.TP
.B update \fI\,[config]\/\fR
Update dotfile configurations. If no config is specified, updates all installed configurations
.TP
.B remove \fI\,<config>\/\fR
Remove an installed dotfile configuration
.TP
.B download \fI\,<config>\/\fR
Download or clone a dotfile configuration repository without installing
.TP
.B cron \fI\,[add|remove|run]\/\fR
Manage automatic dotfile updates via cron job
.TP
.B version \fI\,<config>\/\fR
Display version information for an installed dotfile configuration
